and she had a bad reaction.

166
00:13:30,060 --> 00:13:31,227
BILL:
What did she take?

167
00:13:32,354 --> 00:13:35,731
A speedball or a snowball
or whatever the hell they call it.

168
00:13:35,941 --> 00:13:37,775
It's heroin and coke.

169
00:13:40,737 --> 00:13:42,738
BILL:
Heroin and coke?

170
00:13:45,242 --> 00:13:46,575
Anything else?

171
00:13:48,245 --> 00:13:51,497
We had a couple of drinks,
some champagne. That was it.

172
00:13:51,957 --> 00:13:53,666
How long has she been like this?

173
00:13:54,126 --> 00:13:57,336
Maybe five minutes, six minutes,
something like that.

174
00:13:57,546 --> 00:13:58,671
What's her name?

175
00:13:59,965 --> 00:14:01,048
Mandy.

176
00:14:04,428 --> 00:14:05,886
Mandy?

177
00:14:07,347 --> 00:14:08,681
Mandy?

178
00:14:10,600 --> 00:14:12,476
Can you hear me, Mandy?

179
00:14:13,937 --> 00:14:17,440
Can you hear me?
Move your head if you can hear me.

180
00:14:18,942 --> 00:14:22,028
Move your head if you can
hear me, Mandy. There you go.

181
00:14:22,237 --> 00:14:23,821
You can hear me.

182
00:14:24,031 --> 00:14:28,242
Can you open your eyes for me?
Mandy, can you do that?

183
00:14:28,952 --> 00:14:32,288
Let me see you open your eyes.
There you go, come on.

184
00:14:32,497 --> 00:14:35,499
Come on, look at me. Look at me.

185
00:14:36,043 --> 00:14:38,544
Look at me. Look at me.

186
00:14:39,379 --> 00:14:42,465
Look at me. Look at me, Mandy.

187
00:14:44,134 --> 00:14:45,134
Good.

188
00:14:46,636 --> 00:14:48,012
Good.

189
00:14:49,931 --> 00:14:53,267
I love Victor's art collection,
don't you?

190
00:14:55,687 --> 00:14:56,854
Yes.

191
00:14:57,189 --> 00:14:59,065
It's wonderful.

192
00:15:00,609 --> 00:15:03,569
Have you ever seen
his sculpture gallery?

193
00:15:05,447 --> 00:15:06,739
No.

194
00:15:07,866 --> 00:15:09,575
I haven't.

195
00:15:10,368 --> 00:15:15,164
He has a wonderful collection
of Renaissance bronzes.

196
00:15:17,375 --> 00:15:19,502
Do you like the period?

197
00:15:22,714 --> 00:15:24,381
I do.

198
00:15:25,008 --> 00:15:27,176
I adore it.

199
00:15:29,262 --> 00:15:31,722
The sculpture gallery is upstairs.

200
00:15:33,183 --> 00:15:35,184
Would you like to see it?

201
00:15:38,271 --> 00:15:40,064
I can show it to you.

202
00:15:43,652 --> 00:15:45,569
We won't be gone long.

203
00:15:52,994 --> 00:15:54,787
Maybe...

204
00:15:57,457 --> 00:16:00,584
...not just...

205
00:16:01,753 --> 00:16:03,170
...now.

206
00:16:21,231 --> 00:16:25,484
That was really one hell
of a scare you gave us, kiddo.

207
00:16:27,070 --> 00:16:28,404
Sorry.

208
00:16:37,455 --> 00:16:39,540
How are you feeling now, Mandy?

209
00:16:41,585 --> 00:16:42,710
Better.

210
00:16:52,345 --> 00:16:56,807
You are a very, very lucky girl.

211
00:16:57,934 --> 00:16:59,310
You know that?

212
00:17:01,563 --> 00:17:03,147
I know.

213
00:17:04,191 --> 00:17:06,525
You're gonna be okay this time.

214
00:17:07,777 --> 00:17:11,030
But you can't keep doing this.

215
00:17:11,781 --> 00:17:13,282
You understand?

216
00:17:15,660 --> 00:17:16,785
Yeah.

217
00:17:17,704 --> 00:17:21,582
You're going to need some rehab.
You know that, don't you?

218
00:17:23,376 --> 00:17:24,960
I know.

219
00:17:27,172 --> 00:17:28,464
Okay.

220
00:17:30,217 --> 00:17:31,425
Okay.

221
00:17:36,306 --> 00:17:37,348
Well, Victor...

222
00:17:39,517 --> 00:17:41,101
...I'll leave the rest to you.

223
00:17:41,311 --> 00:17:44,063
Is it okay if I dress her
and get her out of here?

224
00:17:44,272 --> 00:17:47,983
No, I'd keep her here
for another hour.

225
00:17:48,193 --> 00:17:49,693
Another hour?

226
00:17:51,363 --> 00:17:54,531
Then I'd have someone take her home.

227
00:17:55,659 --> 00:17:58,244
Okay. Okay.

228
00:18:00,580 --> 00:18:02,081
Good night, Mandy.

229
00:18:02,290 --> 00:18:03,791
Listen...

230
00:18:05,043 --> 00:18:07,253
I can't thank you enough for this.

231
00:18:08,004 --> 00:18:10,214
- You saved my ass.
- I'm glad I was here.

232
00:18:10,423 --> 00:18:12,883
Bill, I probably...

233
00:18:13,677 --> 00:18:17,263
I know I don't have to mention this...

234
00:18:17,514 --> 00:18:20,391
...but this is just between us.

235
00:18:20,892 --> 00:18:22,142
Of course.

236
00:18:22,686 --> 00:18:23,936
Thanks.

237
00:18:44,958 --> 00:18:49,545
I think I've had
a little too much champagne.

238
00:18:52,674 --> 00:18:56,260
I think I have to go
and find my husband now.

239
00:18:56,469 --> 00:19:01,098
But I'm sure he'll be all right
on his own a little longer.

240
00:19:03,643 --> 00:19:05,019
Yes...

241
00:19:06,438 --> 00:19:08,063
...but will I?

242
00:19:08,732 --> 00:19:10,441
Of course you will.

243
00:19:13,486 --> 00:19:14,778
No.

244
00:19:15,572 --> 00:19:19,408
I really have to go.
I have to go.

245
00:19:19,617 --> 00:19:21,410
You don't, you know.

246
00:19:23,121 --> 00:19:25,748
Yes, I do.

247
00:19:27,000 --> 00:19:28,167
Alice?

248
00:19:31,087 --> 00:19:32,921
I must see you again.

249
00:19:34,758 --> 00:19:37,343
- That's impossible.
- Why?

250
00:19:38,845 --> 00:19:40,596
Because...

251
00:19:43,183 --> 00:19:45,434
...I'm married.

252
00:20:50,333 --> 00:20:51,792
BILL:
Good morning, Lisa.

253
00:20:52,001 --> 00:20:54,128
Good morning, doctor.
Your mail.

254
00:20:54,337 --> 00:20:57,256
Good. Please ask Janelle
to bring me my coffee.

255
00:20:57,465 --> 00:20:59,091
- Sure.
- Thank you.

256
00:20:59,676 --> 00:21:02,636
- Good morning, Sarah.
- Good morning, doctor.

257
00:21:02,846 --> 00:21:05,889
<i>"'Twas the night before Christmas,
when all through the house...</i>

258
00:21:06,099 --> 00:21:08,976
<i>...not a creature was stirring,
not even a mouse. "</i>

259
00:21:13,148 --> 00:21:15,732
Okay. That's fine.
You can put your gown on.

260
